1.title: RiseUp - A Network of Entrepreneurs
1.plot: The story of the beginning of the RiseUp to be a Well known Entrepreneurship Platform in the Middle East and Africa. Launched by Abdel Hamid Sharara and Kon O'Donnell in 2013 to create a network of entrepreneurs gathering and creating a link between them to provide financial support and resources to grow their own businesses.

2.title: Seeloz
2.plot: The story of Seeloz - an online platform that allows business owners to use their data to build an effective marketing plan and choose the best for their customers.

3.title: Paxeramed - Innovative Health
3.plot: Paxeramed develops a full range of medical imaging solutions including multimodality workstations, advanced visualization and enterprise solutions.

4.title: Cloudera - IT Revolution
4.plot: The story of Cloudera which turned from an emerging idea of a young Egyptian entrepreneur into a $ 4 billion company provides Apache Hadoop-based software, support and services, and training to business customers.

5.title: Instabug
5.plot: Instabug is providing in-app feedback and bug reporting to mobile apps. It provides a seamless way for two-way communication with users, while providing detailed environment report for developers.

6.title: Lomar - Reimagining the Arab Dress
6.plot: With only one sewing machine in the house, and then gradually turned into a huge regional factory, becoming one of the largest design and fashion companies in the Gulf, serving more than 150,000 customers.

7.title: UTURN Entertainment
7.plot: In 2010, Saudi entrepreneur Kaswara Al Khatib launched Uturn to start a journey of producing an entertaining content on the online media platforms, reaching millions of viewers in the Middle East.

8.title: Rwaq - A Leading MOOCs Platform
8.plot: In 2013, Rawaq started its journey to become one of the largest MOOcs platforms that offer free academic materials in Arabic in various fields and disciplines.

9.title: Fetcher - Smart Packages
9.plot: In 2012, Idris Al Refaey, together with Omar Yaghmour and Joy Ajlouni, established a promising startup to facilitate shipping operations using an application for smart phones called Fetcher. They secured their first financing in 2013 of $1.5 million. On May 16, 2017, the company announced that it had received US $41 million of investments to expand globally and develop technologies as the leading shipping and delivery company, and to harness technology to revolutionize the sector by eliminating the need for traditional address and use Innovative technological ...

10.title: Service Market - Smart Home Services
10.plot: A promising startup launched in Dubai in 2013 to provide innovative solutions in the field of maintenance, cleaning and transport services, through an online platform that allows users to identify the services they need in a large and growing areas.

11.title: Namshi - Innovative Fashion Market
11.plot: "Namshi" an Online shopping startup specializes in fashion. Launched in 2011 the UAE, seeking to provide fashion, clothing and accessories from more than 400 brands.

12.title: The GrEEk Campus - Entrepreneurs Place
12.plot: In an unusual way, Ahmad al-Alfi and Tariq Ali Taha agreed on the idea of converting the Greek Campus of the American University into a large innovation park offering state-of-the-art office spaces for both startups as well as established multinational technology and media companies and promotes innovation and entrepreneurship in the heart of Cairo. They were inspired by the historical Greek building that is part of the campus while playing on the word "GEEK", a label for many tech-gurus and creative in the industry.

13.title: Carriage - Online Food Ordering and Delivery Revolution
13.plot: Carriage is a leading app in online food ordering and delivery in the Middle East which offers the fastest food delivery service in the Middle East with estimated average delivery time of 40 minutes with GPS live tracking that allow you to view your order while being delivery to your premises.

14.title: Rehlat - Adventure Is the Key to Success
14.plot: Rehlat is a leading online flights and hotels booking service in Middle East.

15.title: QBIC - Qatar Business Incubation Center
15.plot: QBIC is a unique mixed-use business incubation center providing support services to help entrepreneurs and companies who either have an idea to start a business or want to grow an existing business.

16.title: Tamatem - Arabic Games Publisher
16.plot: Tamatem is a Jordanian mobile game developer and publisher, which localizes globally published mobile games and develops their own games for Arabic speakers. It is the leading mobile games publisher in the MENA market.

17.title: ScreenDy - Mobile Apps Reinvented
17.plot: ScreenDy is the next generation of cloud programming software where they mixed the best parts of programming tools and platforms in one cloud programming tool. It makes mobile development easier, faster and more fun than ever before in the market.

18.title: Souq.com - the Middle East's online marketplace
18.plot: Souq connects people and products - opening up a world of possibility. From bracelets and backpacks to tablets and toy cars - Souq give their customers the access to everything they need and want.

19.title: Qatar Science and Technology Park
19.plot: Qatar Science and Technology Park is a home for international technology companies in Qatar, and an incubator of start-up technology businesses.

20.title: Daba Doc - A story of a doctor appointment
20.plot: DabaDoc is the largest online medical appointment booking platform in Africa. DabaDoc is a free service for patients, allowing them to easily find and book an appointment 24/7 with an available doctor nearby that meets their needs. DabaDoc was founded in 2014, with the clear mission to connect patients and doctors, substantially improving the doctor discovery process for patients and helping doctors optimize their schedule.

21.title: Berytech
21.plot: Initiated in 2002 by the Saint-Joseph University, Berytech provides a dynamic environment for the creation and development of startups fostering innovation, technology and entrepreneurship.

22.title: Flat6Labs - Business Acceleration Pioneers
22.plot: Flat6Labs is a regional startup accelerator program that fosters and invests in bright and passionate entrepreneurs with cutting-edge ideas. They provide seed funding, strategic mentorship, a creative workspace, a multitude of perks, entrepreneurship-focused business training, and directly support their startups through an expansive network of partner entities, mentors and investors.

23.title: Mobinets - Networks transformed
23.plot: Mobinets answers the challenges facing today's mobile operator with the most powerful combination of OSS solutions available to give the users greatest control and visibility across their network and help them make the smartest decisions every time. They call that "Network transformation"

24.title: Mixed Dimensions - 3D printing re-imagined
24.plot: Mixed Dimensions is a tech startup founded in 2011 by Muhannad Taslaq, and Baha Abu Nojaim, and incorporated in 2013 shortly after joining the Alchemist Accelerator.

25.title: Oasis500 - Oasis of Technology and Creativity
25.plot: Oasis500 is the leading seed investment company and business accelerator in the Tech and Creative Industry spaces based in Amman, Jordan. They enable great entrepreneurs to transform their viable ideas or creative talents into scalable businesses. That includes finding those entrepreneurs, investing in their startups, bridging their know-how gap, and eventually helping them get follow-on funding. In the process, they have become one of the most influential players in advancing the entrepreneurship and innovation ecosystem in Jordan and the MENA region in general.

26.title: Eat - A onestop for Booking a Table
26.plot: EatApp is a onestop for Booking a Table online at restaurants in Dubai and Bahrain. which you can make online reservations using their website or their App. And at the same time, the application helps restaurants to facilitate their work, building a database of customers and offer effective promotions.

27.title: Yaoota - Smart Shopping Guide
27.plot: Yaoota is a smart search engine specializing in e-shopping and price comparison. It is the first of its kind. started in Egypt and expanded in the Gulf to reach more than 100 electronic stores in 2017, with more than two million seven hundred thousand different products.

28.title: Urban Point - Enjoy your city for less
28.plot: Urban Point is a growing mobile marketplace that connects trendy consumers with quality businesses in Doha by promoting great value offers.

29.title: Mocha Hunters - Coffee hunters
29.plot: "Mocha Hunters" is a US Yemeni startup that aims to revive Yemen's coffee industry and enable the crop to regain its global reputation.

30.title: Ibtikar - A new generation of entrepreneurs
30.plot: Ibtikar (Innovation, in Arabic) Fund is a disruptive fund that invests in innovative Palestinian companies at their earliest stages. Ibtikar's investments begin at the seed level through local accelerators, continue in post-acceleration phases and can also include series A investments in its portfolio companies. Through this investment strategy, they close a critical funding gap between acceleration and VC and other later-stage investors. This documentary film "Ibtikar" discusses it's story and it's founders journey, aired on AlJazeera Channel as part of "...

31.title: Scriptr - Future of the Internet of Things
31.plot: Scriptr - the award winning, managed service and enterprise IoT application marketplace. It's the easiest way to connect your devices to the internet: Build elegant projects that benefit from cloud scalability and java script simplicity. This documentary discusses it's story and it's founders journey.

1.title: Talabat.Com - Seizing Opportunities
1.plot: Throughout time, there have always been that someone who always took the risk of getting a new idea that might change history and shape a new future. Lately, in the Arab region, several youth has shown they have the potential of leaders by making projects that worth millions of dollars, which eventually added up to the overall national economy But we still need more, so iFG Media Group is presenting Entrepreneurs in which you can see an inside view of the success stories of these startups from the first day of their journey, documenting every obstacle they faced and ...

2.title: NAS Trends - Young Ideas on a Shirt
2.plot: An inspiring story of an astonishing startup that started with only couple of thousands of Egyptian pounds shared between college students.

3.title: Arab Weather - Weather Forecasting Pioneer
3.plot: The story of Arabia Weather Foundation, which provides weather and meteorological services in an accurate way exactly like the services provided by global organizations, in addition to its efforts in raising people's awareness of the weather conditions.

4.title: Fi Technologies - Internet for Ads
4.plot: Majid Lababidi's journey to make his idea see the light from Syria, where he began and tried there until he reached Qatar to participate in "Stars of Science" program, then after many terminals between countries, he got an offer from Saad Al-Qahtani, who met him in the program to finance the idea and create "Fi Technologies"

5.title: Ariika - A Leading Egyptian Furniture Company
5.plot: The story of "Ariika" one of Egypt's leading companies in furniture industry. Its team was able to achieve unexpected growth in the past five years since its inauguration, which helped them to be on the top quickly and move their project from the start-up stage to be among the the top ranked companies.

6.title: ITG
6.plot: The story of one of the companies specialized in educational solutions, and one of the leading companies in the technology sector as its business activities cover the local, regional and global markets and the export rate constitutes 85% of the total business of the company.

7.title: Game Cooks - A Unique Arabic Games
7.plot: The first Arab video design and development company, launched in 2012, with a group of artists, developers and game designers who are developing games related to the Middle East and North Africa.

8.title: Middle East Venture Partners "MEVP"
8.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

9.title: Zoomaal - Everyone Finances His Success
9.plot: The story of Zoomaal, the largest Arab crowdfunding platform, started with Abdullah Al Absi, who began the journey with the other colleagues who joined him along the way to reach this milestone of success continue its mission to help entrepreneurs and innovators to make their dreams come true.

10.title: Kharabeesh - Creative Digital Entertainment
10.plot: Kharabeesh is one of the Arab media networks that provides youthful and spontaneous content that supports the creativity of Arab youth on the Internet and represents the new form of digital media broadcasting.

11.title: Mawdoo3.com
11.plot: The story of Mawdoo3.com, which is one of the Arabic Online Encyclopedias, which exploited the rapid spread of the Internet recently and took on the task of enriching the Arabic content on the Internet, and attract the knowledge of books and minds to the field of online encyclopedias.

12.title: UCAS - Future of Gaza
12.plot: UCAS is one of the most important technology incubators in the Arab world, it is located in Gaza, providing an appropriate working environment with the required logistics, in addition to the basic funding according to the nature and needs of the project, and also marketing campaigns for products.

13.title: POYNT - Future of Online Payment
13.plot: POYNT is a startup company in the field of electronic payment services, established by Osama Bedir after considerable experience gained through his work in PayPal systems and Google e-payment portfolio.
